s\nwe will discuss in the lectures. The highlights of the present lectures are:\n  1. Emergence of an (almost) perfect hydrodynamic fluid at late proper-times\nafter the collision.\n  2. Duality between an expanding 4-dimensional plasma and a black hole moving\nradially in the bulk.\n  3. Intimate link between conformal hydrodynamics and Einstein's equations in\nthe asymptotically AdS space.\n  4. Possibility of studying the far-from-equilibrium stage of a gauge field\ntheory at early collisional proper-times.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 3 Feb 2011 16:30:43 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 15 Feb 2011 11:16:15 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 19 Apr 2011 09:22:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-07-26"}
